                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.24/654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-05T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 5, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>337. Your 874, May 3, 5 p.m., last paragraph. The Department desires that in your
                    discretion you endeavor to discourage proposed approach by inviting attention of
                    appropriate quarters to considerations mentioned in the penultimate paragraph of
                    enclosure to the Department’s instruction no. 1455 of May 1.<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d514fn9">See footnote 97, <ref target="#pg_529">p. 529</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
